=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Chain MOVE01 + REVR02) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  MOVE01 -> calc stage 0
C  REVR02 -> calc stage 1 reverses field 02
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars)
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: when calc slot 1 is a parsed REVR over field 01 or 02, the
  runtime now lets that decoded metadata pick the matching two-output detail
  definition instead of leaving short-vs-long output selection fixed to
  calc slot 0.
- Placeholder today: this is still only the current tiny MOVE/REVR subset,
  not a general multi-step C-spec executor or general O-spec selector.

Current runtime-produced output:
A10
B20
C30

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_chain_move1_revr2.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
